Package main

Class Game

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.Game
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable
    public class Game
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
    The game class will handle all of this project's runnable classes. Therefore this class is the only Runnable class in the project. It uses Threads a bufferStrategy as well as the keyManager.

            int width,

    • Method Detail

      • init

        public void init()
        the init method will be runned onced, this method is the first noncontructor method to be called in the class (after the start method). here, the Game will create a display with the current keyManager. initialize the assets of the Assets class and create all the GameStates.

      • tick

        public void tick()
        ticks all the tick method of all the classes and 1 gameState

      • render

        public void render()
        the render method uses a bufferstrategy and will set to draw from the current gamestate and clean everything afterwards

      • run

        public void run()
        the run method will be called after the game's start method. the FPS is set to 30. this method will be called the tick and render method will the game is running
        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable

      • start

        public void start()
